    // Also, by comparing S(3) = pS(2) + qS(1), we have 9 = 4p + q.
    // We can solve these two equations to find p and q.
    // 19 = 9p + 4q
    // 9 = 4p + q
    // Multiply the second equation by 4: 36 = 16p + 4q
    // Subtract the first equation from this: 36 - 19 = 16p + 4q - (9p + 4q) => 17 = 7p => p = 17/7
    // Substitute p = 17/7 into 9 = 4p + q: 9 = 4(17/7) + q => 9 = 68/7 + q => q = 9 - 68/7 = 63/7 - 68/7 = -5/7
    // Therefore, pq = (17/7)(-5/7) = -85/49.
    // The answer is -85/49.
    return "-85/49";
